  "notes": [
    "MI-1040 fillable PDF from Michigan Department of Treasury. 3 pages: page 1 (identity + exemptions + lines 10-17), page 2 (lines 18-34), page 3 (lines 35-40 + refund + signature).",
    "Filing status is on line 7: 7a=Single, 7b=MFJ, 7c=MFS (requires spouse name). No HOH or QSS checkbox — MI maps HOH to Single and QSS to a distinct marital status.",
    "Residency is on line 8: 8a=Resident, 8b=Nonresident, 8c=Part-Year Resident.",
    "SSN is split into 3 widgets: FSSN1 (3 digits), FSSN2 (2 digits), FSSN3 (4 digits).",
    "Line 10 = AGI from federal 1040 line 11. Line 11 = additions. Line 12 = line 10 + 11. Line 13 = subtractions. Line 14 = adjusted taxable income. Line 15 = exemption allowance. Line 16 = taxable income. Line 17 = tax."
  ],
